history.content: Unfortunately, to meet the requirements for 16A, you would need to be a declared CS major.  Since this is the first semester of this course, and it will be highly impacted, we're encouraging all undeclared CS majors to take either EE20 or 40 or wait another semester to enroll in 16A.  It's probably best you can put your phase I units to better use.  Feel free email me with any other questions.

children.subject: Hi Abhi,  I believe the TeleBEARS "bug" was actually not that, but the system did not prompt you to select a secondary section because you don't fit the requirements.  If you are able to get into this course later on, I would adjust the settings and then you would be able to get the sections you need.
Ah, OK, that makes sense. Thanks again!

Thanks for the information, I appreciate it! However, as I plan to be declared next semester and really would prefer to take 16A sooner rather than later, I think I will stay on the waitlist. I made it into CS 70 this semester in a similar situation after waitlisting the course in Phase I.

I am still curious about the possible Tele-BEARS bug/unusual behavior that I mentioned in my original post, though.

history.content: Hi, I just had my Tele-BEARS Phase I appointment and added myself to the waitlist for EE 16A. However, I was not prompted to add any lab/discussion sections (even though they had space available) and was unable to even add them manually using their CCNs. Is this standard for any course when the lecture is full but the secondary sections are not? If it matters, I am currently an undeclared L&S CS freshman with junior unit standing.
